# Binding `T` to `String?` in `first`'s `T?` return collapses to
# `String?` (never the unwritable `String??`): the "empty list" and
# "first element is null" absences merge into one `null`, matching
# the runtime, which delivers both through the same channel.
val maybe_names: List<String?> = [null, "ada"]
val display: String = first(maybe_names) ?? "anonymous"
